Submitting desired feedback to VRChat's [https://feedback.vrchat.com Feedback Board], can help the development team implement constructive changes to the platform.

== Overview ==
{{Thumb|{{YouTube|2nFVVMXqAaE|360px|9 / 16|thumb=File:YTThumb_2nFVVMXqAaE_Severance.webp|title=Tupper…? #Severance #VRChat #vrchatcommunity
}}|Short about VRChat's Feedback Board.<ref>[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=2nFVVMXqAaE Tupper…?] on ''YouTube''.</ref>}}You cannot submit feedback directly within VRChat, but you can post and browse feedback, pseudonymously on {{VRC link|https://feedback.vrchat.com|feedback.vrchat.com}} if you have a VRChat account. The platform uses a ticketing system powered by Canny.io, while VRChat employs a separate internal system to manage and track tickets.

=== Logging in ===
To begin submitting feedback, please go to [https://feedback.vrchat.com feedback.vrchat.com], and proceed to Log In with your [[Special:MyLanguage/VRChat account|VRChat account]]. If you do not yet have a VRChat account, please proceed to [https://vrchat.com/home/register create one on the VRChat website], and optionally, [[Special:MyLanguage/Account Linking|link the accounts]] together.
[[File:Canny.webp|thumb]]
Choose a topic that pertains to your feedback. Please also browse through the rest of the topic names, in case if the feedback can be submitted in a more specific thread.

* '''<u>Feature Requestss:</u>''' ''For general bug reports on primary VRChat client builds.''
* '''<u>Open Beta:</u>''' ''For any bug reports that have occurred on an [[Special:MyLanguage/Open Beta|Open Beta]] build of VRChat.''
* <u>'''Website:'''</u> ''For feedback regarding any of VRChat's websites.''
* '''<u>World/Udon Bugs & Feature Requests:</u>''' ''For feedback regarding [[Special:MyLanguage/Worlds|Worlds]], [[Special:MyLanguage/Udon|Udon]], and [[Special:MyLanguage/Soba|Soba]].''
* '''<u>SDK Bug & Feature Requests:</u>''' ''For feedback with the [[Special:MyLanguage/VRChat SDK|VRChat SDK]].''
* '''<u>Localization:</u>''' ''For feedback regarding language support, translation, and localization.''
* '''<u>VRC+ Feature Ideas:</u>''' ''For feature requests and feedback regarding [[Special:MyLanguage/VRC+|VRC+]].''
* '''<u>Merch Ideas:</u>''' ''For feedback, and ideas regarding official VRChat [[Special:MyLanguage/Merchandise|Merchandise]].''

Once a topic is selected, you can search various community threads to see if another user has already posted similar ideas and feedback. If so, it is highly encouraged to upvote the post, and leave a comment if any specifications are not listed. If there is not a post that is yet submitted regarding feedback, please begin writing a bug report. Optionally, share the feedback post with friends and encourage them to upvote your post.

== Regarding feedback ==
[[File:Canny topfeedback.webp|thumb|Top feedback on VRChat's "Feature Requests" board, as of February 2026.]]
After submitting feedback, it may take a while for your post to be acknowledged. Providing feedback on features currently being implemented in [[Special:MyLanguage/Open Beta|Open Beta]] are more likely to be acknowledged in a shorter time frame, as features become developed and implemented. VRChat's development team reads all feedback posted to the Feedback Board, but may not always provide immediate interactions with posts.

Despite this, it is still encouraged for users to provide constructive feedback at any time, and express patience. Feedback posts can be upvoted by other VRChat community members, and typically, VRChat may set a priority to implement feedback with more upvotes. It is also encouraged for users to browse the Feedback Board, and upvote any ideas that they agree with.

